The Premier League has released the list of nominees for February’s Player of the Month award. They include Pierre-Emerick Aubameyang (Arsenal), Bruno Fernandes (Manchester United), Matt Doherty (Wolverhampton Wanderers), Marcos Alonso (Chelsea) and Dominic Calvert-Lewin (Everton). Fans have until 6pm on March 9 to vote for their favourite players. The public’s votes will then be combined with those of the 20 club captains and a panel of football experts to decide the winner next week. Mikel Arteta (Arsenal), Sean Dyche (Burnley), Ole Gunnar Solskjaer (Manchester United) and Chris Wilder are up for the manager’s award.